fields.title: Assignment 1
fields.description:
Create a Django project for a car rental application named "CarApp." The application should allow users to view and rent cars available in the inventory. Design the necessary models, views, and URLs to implement this functionality.

Requirements:

  1. Create a Django project named "CarAppProject."

  2. Inside the project, create an app named "carrental."

  3. Define a model named "Car" to represent car details with the following fields:

    • Make (CharField)
    • Model (CharField)
    • Year (PositiveIntegerField)
    • Price (DecimalField)
    • Availability (BooleanField)
    • Image (ImageField)

  4. Implement views to handle the following functionalities:

    • Display a list of available cars in the inventory.
    • View details of a specific car, including its make, model, year, price, and image.
    • Allow users to rent a car (change availability status) when viewing car details.

  5. Design URLs to map the views:

    • URL pattern for displaying the list of available cars should be "cars/".
    • URL pattern for viewing details of a specific car should be "cars/int:car_id/".
    • URL pattern for renting a car should be "cars/int:car_id/rent/".

  6. Implement templates to render the views with appropriate HTML structure and CSS styling.

  7. Ensure proper error handling and display user-friendly messages when needed (e.g., when a car is not available for rent).

Note: You can use any frontend framework (e.g., Bootstrap) or custom CSS to enhance the UI.

Submission: Submit the Django project folder (CarAppProject) along with the "carrental" app folder, including all the necessary files (models.py, views.py, urls.py, templates, etc.), and a README file (if any specific instructions are needed to run the project).
